  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Compliance Officer",
  "description": "<p>The Compliance Officer reports directly to the Head of Compliance.<br /></p><p>He/she is responsible for the following:</p><ul><li>Perform and conduct periodic AML/CFT screening on customers and counterparties upon requests of stakeholders in the bank, using the bank's designated screening system, including the bank's KYC consolidated list.</li><li>Assist to purchase company registration information/financials from company registrar, e.g. Accounting and Corporate Regulatory Authority (Singapore), Suruhanjaya Syarikat Malaysia (Malaysia) and Companies Registry (Hong Kong).</li><li>Assist in checking the AML/CFT Review and customer due diligence documents provided by the Relationship Managers (“RM”) in accordance with the bank’s control procedures to ensure compliance with regulatory requirements.</li><li>Maintenance of the central filing and customer’s records, coordination of the retrieval and filing of all compliance documents, including all MAS Circulars. Ensure that the relevant registers are current and up to date.   </li><li>Act as the Data Protection Officer of the bank to ensure all staff are compliant with the Personal Data Protection Act (\"PDPA\") through email communications and training.</li><li>Attend to all ad-hoc requests received from authorities / courts.</li><li>Deputise the Head of Compliance when she is not in the office, including attendance at meetings when required.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc tasks as assigned by the Head of Compliance.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree in Business or related subjects, compliance qualifications are preferred.</li><li>At least 2-3 years of working experience in the area of AML/CFT, and compliance in financial industries.</li><li>Comprehensive understanding of regulatory requirements in the banking industry.</li><li>Proven ability to work independently without constant oversight. Takes ownership of responsibilities and demonstrates initiative in handling tasks and provide ideas and solutions proactively.</li><li>Meticulous and focused in delivering high quality work.</li></ul>",
